tanism is just evil, and those that practice it are potentially harmful to those around them.<br>
<br>
There are no boundaries to a Satanist, no limits to a Satanist. If a Satanist wants to enslave a population, or molest children, or poison the town's water supply, or anything at all he wants to do, no matter how outrageous or cruel, if he feels he can do it and get away with it, there is no reason for him not to. Other people, their rights, their happiness, indeed their very lives do not even enter into the equation for a Satanist. &quot;Self&quot; is the only consideration.<br>
<br>
I am not exaggerating this, or mischaracterizing Satanism. It is all spelled out clearly, in so many words, in the writings of Anton LaVey and Aleister Crowely that SELF is all that matters. Everyone and everything else are simply resources to be exploited and then discarded at the whim of Self, or obstacles to be circumvented or destroyed if Self perceives them to be in the way. Evil. <p>__________<br>
<i>"All along the untrodden paths of the future, I see the footprints of an unseen hand."</i><br>
